---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Hero from '@/components/Hero.astro';
import CTABlock from '@/components/CTABlock.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="What is Lush Kitchen?"
  description="An explainer on the Lush Kitchen subscription box: exclusive products, returning favourites, and a properly passionate community."
>
  <Hero
    title="What is Lush Kitchen?"
    tag="For the uninitiated"
    minimal
  />

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container container--narrow">
      <div class="page-content">
        <p>
          If you've found this site and you're thinking "what even is Kitchen?", welcome, you're in
          the right place.
        </p>

        <h3>The short version</h3>
        <p>
          Lush Kitchen is a monthly subscription box from Lush. You pay a set price, and every month
          a box turns up with a mix of exclusive products, returning favourites, and sometimes
          completely new experimental stuff. You don't get to choose what's in it, and that's half the fun.
        </p>

        <h3>What's actually in the box?</h3>
        <p>
          Usually 4-6 products. Could be bath bombs, bubble bars, shower gels, soaps, body lotions,
          basically anything Lush makes. Some months lean harder into bath products, some months are
          more body care focused. The mix changes and that's what keeps it interesting.
        </p>
        <p>
          The exciting bit is that a lot of these products are Kitchen exclusives. You literally
          can't get them anywhere else. Some are brand new creations, some are discontinued
          fan favourites brought back for one more run. OGs will remember the old Kitchen before
          it was a subscription, where you'd vote on products and order them individually. Different era,
          same energy.
        </p>

        <h3>The community</h3>
        <p>
          Ngl, the Kitchen community is one of the best bits. Everyone's genuinely into it, swapping
          scent notes, debating which month was the strongest, getting properly excited when a
          discontinued favourite comes back. It's not performative, people just really love this stuff.
        </p>
        <p>
          There's a real thing that happens when a product from like 2015 turns up in a box and
          everyone collectively loses it. That shared nostalgia is what makes Kitchen special.
        </p>

        <h3>Why I'm obsessed</h3>
        <p>
          I've been subscribed since February 2022 and haven't missed a month. Some boxes are
          absolute bangers, some are a bit mid ngl, but even the quieter months have at least
          one product that surprises me. The surprise element is genuinely addictive.
        </p>
        <p>
          If you're thinking about subscribing, defo do it. Even if you end up giving away a
          product or two each month, it's worth it for the ones that become instant favourites.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CTABlock
    title="See every box"
    description="Browse the full archive of every Kitchen box I've received since 2022."
    primaryLink="/kitchen-boxes/"
    primaryLabel="Kitchen Box Archive"
    secondaryLink="/my-lush-story/"
    secondaryLabel="My Lush Story"
  />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-content {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-md);
  }

  .page-content h3 {
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .page-content p {
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    line-height: 1.85;
    max-width: none;
  }
</style>
